00:02:46.510 --> 00:02:51.950
Despite being an amazing source of both nutrition
and pleasure, breasts are incredibly vulnerable.

00:02:51.950 --> 00:02:55.840
Breast cancer is the most prevalent form of
cancer in North America. Cells that divide

00:02:55.840 --> 00:03:00.620
often are at a higher risk of mutations than
cells that don’t divide - and because breasts

00:03:00.620 --> 00:03:04.980
change and grow over the course of our lives,
these cells are frequently dividing. The hormone

00:03:04.980 --> 00:03:09.310
estrogen also stimulates breast cell division,
and there are environmental chemicals found

00:03:09.310 --> 00:03:13.840
in pesticides, industrial products, and even
our food that mimic estrogen and can influence

00:03:13.840 --> 00:03:18.560
cell growth, increasing the risk of breast
cancer. Research is discovering new risk factors

00:03:18.560 --> 00:03:23.230
of breast cancer such as breast density, age
of first pregnancy, and genetic predisposition

00:03:23.230 --> 00:03:29.480
to breast cancer genes such as BRCA1 and BRCA2.
This scientific knowledge can help increase

00:03:29.480 --> 00:03:30.480
prevention.

00:03:30.480 --> 00:03:35.060
Although they are vulnerable, they are incredible,
and regardless of shapes and sizes they are

00:03:35.060 --> 00:03:40.840
an essential aspect of sustaining human life
and defining us as a species. Thank you boobs.

